data.description: Exceptional Opportunity in Montecito Park, Glendale After 44 years, this charming 3-bed, 2-bath residence makes its debut on the market! Nestled in the coveted Montecito Park neighborhood renowned for serene seclusion, beautiful oak trees, and wonderful wildlife. Meticulously maintained home exudes warmth and awaits its new chapter. Elevated from the street, revel in unparalleled privacy. Fully enclosed patio garden, new custom shed with stairs leading to a tiered level space ready for a garden or secluded area with mature lemon and fig trees. Beautiful natural rock fireplace in living room and oversized den perfect for entertaining with separate access to patios. Large formal dining room with oversized windows and built-in oak china cabinet. Situated within acclaimed school districts, moments from Montrose Village, Descanso Gardens, and just minutes from Angeles Crest Forest. Enjoy proximity to Cherry Canyon Park, Glendale Community College, and seamless access to 2, 210, and 134 freeways. Home features upgraded dual-  pane vinyl windows, newer AC, copper plumbing, and a 50-year roof installed in 2009!
